      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "This seems like a good idea, as we do have both internal and external API functions that are only constant-time in some subset of the inputs.\r\n\r\nOne perhaps rather small point: functions can be constant-time or non-constant-time in their *output* too. E.g. an ECDH function that first computes a point multiplication (constant time in both its point and scalar argument) and then applies a variable-time hashing algorithm on its output. This may or may not be fine if the output of the function is not used as a secret-to-be-protected. Should that too be encoded in the naming somehow?",
      "user": {
